# Contour - KX Dashboards

Original URL: https://code.kx.com/dashboards/contour/

# Contour

![Screenshot](../img/contour/contourchart.jpg)

Contour plots are a way to show a three-dimensional surface on a two-
dimensional plane.

## Set up

  1. Add a data source.

  2. Define the X- and Y-Axis to plot.

  3. Shading is defined by the Z-axis and the color gradient. Use the _Tick interval_ to set the gap in the number of display labels for the z-axis. 

## Basics

![Screenshot](../img/contour/contourbasics.png)

_Name_

    A name for the component provided by the user. 
_Data Source_

     [Data sources](../datasources/)
_Show Scale Bar_

    Display scale for the response (contour) variable, Z-axis.
_Type_

    

Select between `contour` or `heatmap`

![Screenshot](../img/contour/contourtypes.jpg)

## X-, Y- and Z-Axis

![Screenshot](../img/contour/contouraxis.jpg)

_Column_

    Select data column from _Data Source_.
_Type_

    Select axis type: `linear`, `category` or `date`; `category` and `date` are only available for `heatmap` _Type_ contour charts. 
_Use Range_

_Min_

_Max_

    Set axis range values, axis will default to data range if not set.

Z-axis

Determines the line interpolation and contour colors as defined by range _Min_
and _Max_ , or default data minimum and maximum.

### Title

_Label_

_Label Size_

    Give axis a name and set the font size.

## Layout

![Screenshot](../img/contour/contourlayout.jpg)

_Background_

    Set color background of chart
_Top_

_Bottom_

_Left_

_Right_

    Set chart margins (pixels)
_Pad_

    Set central chart image padding (pixels)

## Palette Theme

     [Palette Theme](../palette/#palette-theme)

## Contour Palette

![Screenshot](../img/contour/contourpalette.jpg)

Sets the number of colors used in the range; range values will be spread
evenly across the number of defined colors.

    

[Palettes](../palette/#palettes)

_Show Annotation_

    Adds overlay of contour values
_Tick Interval_

    Define tick label frequency on gradient bar. 

_Show Tooltip_

    Default to display of x-, y- and z-axis (shade) values; defined in _Custom Tooltip_.
_Custom Tooltip_

    Create a custom tooltip; default sample tooltip used by _Show Tooltip_. 

## Image

_Source_

    Replace map with an image sourced from an URL. Can be a [view state parameter](../viewstateparameters/)

## Style, Margins, Format

![Screenshot](../img/contour/contourstyle.jpg)

_Line Smoothing_

    Determines line smoothing; a value of zero reflects no smoothing, 100 is maximum smoothing. 

[Style](../style/#component-style) for common settings

